CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 11, 1961, p. 2, reads: "Candidates Work Hard in Victory Quest - 'You're Rollin' Pappy! - Committee men and women and other supporters assure Fifth Ward Democratic Aldermanic aspirant, Robert E. (Pappy) Williams, front row center, who won both party nominations in the primary election, that he 'had it made.' - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Women and men surrounding Robert E. "Pappy" Williams outside of brick building, including K. Leroy Irvis wearing eyeglasses standing second row, second from left.
